spans.text: the fair dewy fingers of Spring
my fairest and I sweetly wake
the daisies , and cowslips , and primroses
bounding there the swift lightfooted do
that is ready to fall from her eye
none to create so much love , and surprise , As her eyes , and her face , and her shape
so much love , and surprise , As her eyes
the flowers hang their heads With the dew
hasten to find our way home
by the side of its mate
a missed that arises a drowsiness
the sacred repose of the night
give and receive all the nameless soft joys
